JHFRC Address to Census Tract Converter
========================================

This tool was developed by the Journey Health Foundation Research Center (JHFRC)
at the University of Tennessee at Chattanooga.

It is intended for use by nonprofit partner organizations as part of collaborative
community health research.

---

Geocoding is performed using the U.S. Census Bureau Geocoding Services API,
which is a free public service provided by the U.S. Census Bureau.
  https://geocoding.geo.census.gov/

Census tract boundary data is sourced from the U.S. Census Bureau
TIGER/Line Cartographic Boundary Files, which are in the public domain.
  https://www.census.gov/geographies/mapping-files/time-series/geo/cartographic-boundary.html

